                        <additions>
                            <list>
                                <item xml:id="e1">
                                    <desc>Mentioned in the supplications throughout are <persName ref="PRS13719MezaraK"/>, 
                                        his daughters <persName ref="PRS13720LahyaD"/>, <persName ref="PRS13721LebestaK"/>, and 
                                        his son <persName ref="PRS13722TaklaH"/> (e.g. <locus target="#69vb #108va"/>). The names of the daughters have been added later
                                        between the lines.
                                        All names have often been erased. The colophon indicates that a woman sponsored the production of the manuscript
                                    and donated it to a church. Her name has been erased, but it might be speculated that she was a family member
                                    of the persons mentioned throughout - possibly <persName ref="PRS13720LahyaD"/>, as the last two characters of her name
                                    seem to have been <foreign xml:lang="gez">ግል</foreign>.</desc>
                                </item>
                                
                                <item xml:id="e2">
                                    <locus target="#1r"/>
                                    <desc>Modern stamp.</desc>
                                    <q xml:lang="en">Presented by the Secretary of State for India. <date when="1868">Aug. 1868</date></q>
                                </item>
                            </list>
                            
                        </additions>
                        
